    {
      "component": "menu.trigger",
      "description": "> **Nested Interactivity Constraint:** Do not pass fully interactive components (like standard `button(...)` blocks) as children inside `menu.trigger`. Nesting interactive elements intercepts DOM click events and prevents the menu from opening. To style your trigger like a button, pass raw strings/icons and apply button classes directly to the trigger component.",
      "props": [],
      "example": "menu.trigger(button(\"Open\"))",
      "category": "components"
    },
    {
      "component": "menu.content",
      "description": "> **Layout Boundaries**: This component utilizes pure CSS absolute positioning instead of DOM portaling. The popup menu remains nested deep inside its localized DOM tree node. Ensure that no parent container layouts above this component enforce **overflow: hidden** or **overflow: auto** constraints, as this will physically clip or crop the floating dropdown menu box.",
      "props": [
        {
          "name": "side",
          "type": "`Literal[\"bottom\", \"top\", \"left\", \"right\"]`",
          "default": "`\"bottom\"`"
